		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Cincini</placeName> <date>Oct. 9</date>.</p>
				<p>Rd. Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Herewith I enclose the conclusion of the rejoinder to <persName>D. Wise</persName><lb/> my last correspodena<add>&#63;</add> with you&#44; was written during the confusion caused by removing into our <add>&#63;</add><lb/> House on <placeName>8th St.</placeName> from our <sic>cuntry</sic> retreat.  I should have mentioned to you and also<lb/> noticed it in my article.  One of the causes that urged me to the attempt of agitating<lb/> a call for a conference.  In a private conversation with a wealthy and influential<lb/> person of our city&#44; he remarks that if he were capable to write his sentiments&#44; concer<lb/>ning some of the doubtful questions <del>of</del> that now agitate the public mind&#44; he would<lb/> try hard to get a conference composed of competent men&#44; that would give their final<lb/> verdict and satisfy all parties&#44; he would <sic>cheerfuly</sic> subscribe 500&#36; toward the expenses<lb/> connecting it &#38; &#38;&#44; but as this was private I withhold his name.  I have in this last&#44; <sic>referd</sic> to<lb/> a meeting lately held in lodge L.&#44; a two third was taken on the question of abolishing the 2d<lb/> holiday it was carried to abolish 63. to reclaim 31  The Doctor is now going through the<lb/> City canvasing for Signatures to pledge their names that they will close their<lb/> business on <date>Sab.</date>  I hope he may succeed&#44; as yet he has but few names&#44; <add>&#63;</add><lb/> he has not carried out any of his proposed measures.  I have <sic>endeavord</sic> in my<lb/> humble manner to show the character of the new minag. and to caution<lb/> the public against its adoption&#44; if you will endorse this or give the sentences a<lb/> better expression&#44; so much the better.  I have put my name <del>at</del> and that of <hi rend="underline"><placeName>Cincin</placeName></hi><lb/> at the conclusion.  513 alone would do&#44; but I wish it known&#44; that there are numbers<lb/> in <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> who condemn the course <sic>persued</sic> by the Dr. &#38; his colleagues&#44; nor do<lb/> they allow his paper to be <sic>considerd</sic> their Organ please to notice this&#44; <persName>Mr. P. Bamberger</persName><lb/> says if you will send his a&#47;c on&#44; he will discharge it.  I have filed the weekly Occident<lb/> The whole of them did not reach me&#44; I have collected the missing <hi rend="underline">numbers</hi>.  I am short of<lb/> No. 10.  Could you send this on and charge it&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">In haste</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours Very Respy</p>
			<p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Saml. Bruel</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>The</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><hi rend="underline"><sic><addressee>Revd I Leesor</addressee></sic></hi></p>
